WHO IS ARLINGTON CAPITAL MANAGEMENT?

Arlington Capital Management (ACM) is a privately held, SEC (www.sec.gov) Registered  Investment Advisory (RIA) firm specializing in providing portfolio management services to individuals, families and small businesses.  Founded in 2000, ACM employs a proprietary proactive investment methodology.  Our Proactive Asset Allocation Strategy (PAAS), Proactive Income Strategy and Proactive 401(k) Strategy have all been developed in-house, and all portfolio decisions are made internally by our Investment Policy Committee, chaired by Joseph LoPresti.
As a fee-only RIA, our revenue is solely derived from the fees assessed on assets under our management.  We do not earn commissions of any kind.  As advisors held to the highest fiduciary standards in today’s financial services industry, we are obligated to act in the best interests of our clients. 

Arlington Capital Management currently has $271.8 million in client assets under advisement.  Headquartered in suburban Chicago, we have satellite offices in Houston TX, San Jose CA, Scottsdale AZ,  and Brookfield WI.




























